What if `word_name` is `'123'`? `int('123')` succeeds, raises `ValueError("illegal operation")`. Correct.

One detail: `tokens.extendleft(reversed(words[token]))`
If `words[token]` is `['1', '+']`, `reversed` gives `['+', '1']`. `extendleft` adds `'+'` then `'1'`. Deque becomes `['1', '+', ...]`. Correct.

